suggestingly.translation:
suggestingly
adv.
suggest的变形
suggest
[sə'dʒest; səɡ-]
vt.
提出，提议，建议：
The specialist suggested that children should not eat too much sugar.
专家建议儿童不该吃太多的食糖。
My friend suggested my getting a job in a bank.
我的朋友建议我在银行找个工作。
推荐，举荐：
It was suggested that he be the chairman of the meeting.
他被举荐为大会主席。
(事物)使人想到，使人联想到：
The smell of perfume suggests the girl whom I met in the plane on the way to Lisbon.
这种香水味令我想起了飞往里斯本的航班上遇到的那位姑娘。
The music suggests a still night.
这种音乐令人联想到宁静的夜晚。
(间接地)表明，意思是：
The ring suggests that he was on the scene of the crime.
这只戒指表明他在作案现场。
OK,silence suggests agreement.
对，沉默就表示同意。
暗示：
She suggested that she did not want me to tell the truth.
她暗示我不要说出实情。
He did ignor what I suggeted to him.
他根本不理睬我对他的暗示。
启示，启发；促使做(或思考)：
Having been suggested by a bat, people invented sonar.
受到蝙蝠的启发，人们发明了声呐。
Social development suggests universal exploration.
社会的进步促使人类做出对宇宙空间的探索。
近义词:
hint
. imply
. insinuate
. intimate
短语:
I suggest (that)
照我看，恐怕
suggest itself (或themselves) to
浮现在…的心中(或眼前)
